ArchRWire: Extensions for Co-accessibility Analysis with ArchR¶

R version 4.0.2
ArchRWire version 0.1.01
Vignette for ArchR: https://www.archrproject.com/bookdown/getting-started-with-archr.html
ArchR version 0.9.5

Overview¶

  1. Set up analysis with ArchR and ArchRWire
    a) Install ArchRWire
  2. Load exemplary ArchRProject
  3. Co-accessibility analysis
    a) Get co-accessible links
    b) Inspect co-accessible links
    c) Determine background co-accessibility
    d) Filter co-accessible links by background co-accessibility and cell accessibility thresholds
    e) Inspect filtered co-accessible links
  4. Visualization
    a) Browser tracks with co-accessible links
    b) Co-accessibility maps

1. Set up analysis with ArchR and ArchRWire¶

### Libraries

library(magrittr)
library(ArchR)
library(ggpubr)
library(purrr)
library(devtools)

### Set ArchR parameters.
addArchRThreads(threads = 15) # number of parallel threads
addArchRGenome('hg38') # genome and gene annotation ('hg19', 'hg38', 'mm9', 'mm10')


a) Install ArchRWire¶

setwd('/media/ag-rippe/isabelle/ArchRWire_dev')
with_libpaths(new = "/path/to/your/R4.0.2_libs", install('ArchRWire'))

library(ArchRWire, lib.loc = "/path/to/your/R4.0.2_libs")

3. Co-accessibility analysis¶

overview

a) Get co-accessible links¶

proj <- addCoAccessibility(proj, reducedDims = "IterativeLSI_25000varFeatures", maxDist=1e+06)

### Adapted getCoAccessibility function also reports ratios of accessible cells of linked peaks for filtering
coacc <- ArchRWire::getCoAccessibility(proj, corCutOff = 0, resolution = 1, returnLoops = TRUE)[[1]]

coacc

b) Inspect co-accessible links¶

par(mfrow=c(1,3))
hist(x=coacc$correlation, breaks=100, main='Correlation coefficients of co-accessible links', xlab='Correlation coefficient', xlim=c(0,1))
hist(x=c(coacc$accessCellRatio1, coacc$accessCellRatio2), breaks=100, main='Ratio of accessible cells of co-accessible links', xlab='Ratio of accessible cells', xlim=c(0,1))



c) Determine background co-accessibility¶

background <- ArchRWire::getBackgroundCoAccessibility(proj, reducedDims = "IterativeLSI_25000varFeatures", maxDist=1e+06)

### Visualize cell shuffled and feature shuffled background correlations with 95th, 99th and 100th percentile (red lines)
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
hist(background$cellShuffle$correlation, main="Cell shuffled background", breaks=100, xlab="correlation coefficient")
abline(v=quantile(background$cellShuffle$correlation, seq(0.01,1,by=0.01), na.rm=T)[c(95, 99, 100)], col='darkred') 
hist(background$featShuffle$correlation, main="Feature shuffled background", breaks=100, xlab="correlation coefficient")
abline(v=quantile(background$featShuffle$correlation, seq(0.01,1,by=0.01), na.rm=T)[c(95, 99, 100)], col='darkred')

### Select maximum of 95th, 99th or 100th percentile cutoff (determines how strict the cutoff should be -> maximum 99th percentile cutoff recommended)
pmax(quantile(background$cellShuffle$correlation, seq(0.01,1,by=0.01), na.rm=T)[c(95, 99, 100)], 
     quantile(background$featShuffle$correlation, seq(0.01,1,by=0.01), na.rm=T)[c(95, 99, 100)])
background_cutoff <- pmax(quantile(background$cellShuffle$correlation, seq(0.01,1,by=0.01), na.rm=T)[99], 
     quantile(background$featShuffle$correlation, seq(0.01,1,by=0.01), na.rm=T)[99])
95%
0.077477036643282
99%
0.112204035034822
100%
0.267806978999797



d) Filter co-accessible links by background co-accessibility and cell accessibility thresholds¶

coacc_filtered <- subset(coacc, subset = correlation > background_cutoff & accessCellRatio1 > 0.05 & accessCellRatio2 > 0.05)



e) Inspect filtered co-accessible links¶

### Inspect filtered co-accessible links
par(mfrow=c(1,3))
hist(x=coacc_filtered$correlation, breaks=100, main='Correlation coefficients of co-accessible links', xlab='Correlation coefficient', xlim=c(0,1))
hist(x=c(coacc_filtered$accessCellRatio1, coacc_filtered$accessCellRatio2), breaks=100, main='Ratio of accessible cells of co-accessible links', xlab='Ratio of accessible cells', xlim=c(0,1))



4. Visualization¶

overview

a) Browser tracks with co-accessible links¶

tracks <- ArchRWire::plotBrowserTrack( 
        ArchRProj = proj, 
        groupBy = "Sample",
        geneSymbol = 'Usp18',
        loops =  coacc,
        normMethod = "raw") # ArchRWire enables raw/non-normalized pseudobulk browser tracks

grid::grid.draw(tracks[[1]])



b) Co-accessibility maps¶

maps <- ArchRWire::plotCoAccessibilityMap(proj, region = GRanges(seqnames="chr22", 
                                                                 ranges=IRanges(start = 18100000, end = 18190000)))
